STAT3040 : Time Series Analysis 2016 Computer Lab. 9 - Week 10

1. ARMA Models in R

  1. Generate a time series from the MA(3) model \[ X_t=\mathcal{W}_t + 0.8\mathcal{W}_{t-1} + 0.1\mathcal{W}_{t-2} - 0.7\mathcal{W}_{t-3} \]

  2. Generate a time series from the AR(2) model \[ X_t=X_{t-1} - 0.16 X_{t-2} + \mathcal{W}_{t} \]

  3. Calculate the theoretical ACF and PACF of the AR(2) model \[ X_t=X_{t-1} - 0.16 X_{t-2} + \mathcal{W}_{t} \]

  4. Find the roots of the AR polynomial for the AR(2) model \[ X_t=X_{t-1} - 0.16 X_{t-2} + \mathcal{W}_{t} \]
